Cell.Text: S|I am waiting for a good death.
If you are not here to grant me a good death, then you can leave.
S|Yes. We're I to simply lay down and die, it would not please Mauloch.

S|My time has come. I am old. Too old to become chief. It would be wrong for me to take wives at this age. So I will die. | Mauloch has given me a vision of a glorious death. I am to wait here until it finds me. | As you can see, it has not yet arrived.

Node.Caption: WE24Why: Why do you wish to die?

Cell.Text: Perhaps... | Are you sure about this?

Node.Caption: WE24Help: Perhaps I could give you the death you seek?
WE24Yes: Yes, I am sure. I will give you a good death.

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> You should leave. I don't want you scaring off my good death.

S|Indeed. One should find his death while he can still call himself a proper man. | We Orc men are not like these Nords and Imperials who carry on until they are grey and feeble and their hair falls out. | To cling to something past usefulness is unseemly, how much more so when that thing is you?

Node.Caption: WE24Convince: You don't look that old to me. Certainly you're still a strong capable warrior.

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> Then leave. I don't want you scaring off my good death.

Node.Caption: WE24Goodluck: It seems there's no talking you out of this...
